dismissalText.commentary: Kumar Sangakkara c †Mustard b Broad 9 (25b 0x4 0x6 41m) SR: 36

dismissalComment.html: and he's walked! How extraordinary. Wide of the off stump, Sangakkara cut and missed, the ball flying through to Mustard who didn't appeal. And nor did Broad...but Sangakkara tucked his bat under his arm and marched off. A poor piece of cricket. It was the thinnest of edges, and no England player appealed, yet Sangakkara marched off to cause confused (albeit delighted) expressions from England's fielders

commentTextItems.html: flicked off his pads, just evading the short midwicket and there's the match for England. A great effort from Broad

commentPostTextItems.html: A slight bit of confusion right at the end when Sri Lanka claimed to have run out Sidebottom, but they'd already run the required two runs - and now take a 2-1 series lead. They've played some mediocre cricket today - in fact both sides have; it's been ugly, desperate cricket at times. But, yet again, Broad showed his maturity - as did Swann with the ball in Sri Lanka's innings - to take England home to a vital victory, especially considering the poor weather forecast for the final two fixtures. We hope you've enjoyed our coverage today, and do join us on Wednesday for England's next game. From me, Will Luke, and Martin Williamson, it's goodnight.

commentTextItems.html: full, swinging into Broad - Malinga's desperate to find this yorker but it's not quite working. Broad leans into it and plays a beautiful extra cover drive for four

commentPostTextItems.html: What a shot at such a tense moment

another zippy delivery but it's wild and misdirected down the leg side. Sidebottom gets bat on it and they scamper a single

commentPreTextItems.html: England probably have their noses in front again now. There's now a committee going on out in the middle with Jayawardene counselling opinion from all and sundry. Who's to bowl?

commentTextItems.html: close! So close there. A vicious, swinging ball which evades the off stump...and evades Sidebottom's bat too
guided out to point and they run an easy single
